counter_name_alias: SEIZURE ATTEMPTS
counter_description: Number of times when an MS attempts to seize an SDCCH.

counter_name_alias: SEIZURE ATTEMPTS WITH BUSY SDCCH
counter_description: Number of times when an MS attempts to seize an SDCCH but the attempt is unsuccessful because all SDCCHs are busy. This counter does not necessarily mean that the call attempt is lost, because the call may be established as an FACCH call setup using TCH instead of SDCCH.  This counter is not triggered when the TCH reconfiguration is attempted because of dynamic SDCCH allocation. If the attempt fails, the SDCCH_busy_attempt is triggered together with 1155 UNSUCC_IMM_ASS_SDCCH_ATTEMPT.

counter_name_alias: SUCCESS SEIZURE FOR HO
counter_description: Number of successful SDCCH seizures for a handover.

counter_name_alias: SUCCESS SEIZURE FOR IMMEDIATE ASSIGNMENT
counter_description: Number of successful seizures of SDCCH for an immediate assignment.

counter_name_alias: SUCCESS TCH SEIZURE FOR HO
counter_description: Number of successful requests for a TCH in a handover.

counter_name_alias: SUCCESS TCH SEIZURE FOR NORMAL ASSIGNMENT
counter_description: Number of successful requests for a TCH in a normal assignment.

counter_name_alias: TCH REQUEST SUCCESS AND UNSUCCESS
counter_description: Total number of requests for a TCH (successful and unsuccessful).

counter_name_alias: TCH REQUEST REJECTED DUE TO LACK
counter_description: Number of requests for TCHs that are rejected because there are no radio resources available. All kinds of procedures used to request a TCH are considered, that is, the TCH is rejected if there is no requested resources available for assignments using the normal TCH assignment procedure and assignments for all kinds of (incoming) handovers. This counter is also updated when a request for TCH is rejected because of a mismatch between the types of the requested channel and the A interface circuit.  See also counter 004079.

counter_name_alias: HANDOVER ATTEMPTS IN THE QUEUE
counter_description: Number of HO attempts set in the queue for a TCH.  Counter 001010 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: SDCCH ABIS PROBL
counter_description: Number of SDCCH transactions that are ended because of a failure in the Abis interface.  Impact: - Call cleared - HO failure  Reason for the impact: External / Abis interface

counter_name_alias: SDCCH BTS FAIL
counter_description: Number of SDCCH transactions that are ended because of a BTS failure. (The blocked TRX is in one of these substates: FU fault, CU fault, BTS reset, BCF reset, both CU and FU fault, BCF fault.)  Impact: Call cleared

counter_name_alias: SDCCH NETW ACT
counter_description: Number of SDCCH transactions ended because of a reconfiguration of the radio network. (The TRX blocked is in substate blocked by the system.)  Impact: - Call cleared - HO failure  Reason for the impact: See Radio Network Management, Service Block Description, for radio network reconfiguration.

counter_name_alias: QUE NALL ASSIGN REQ ATT
counter_description: Number of requests for a call attempt with queuing not allowed.  Counter 001010 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: QUE NALL ASSIGN REQ FAIL
counter_description: Number of rejected call attempt requests with queuing not allowed.  Counters 001011 and 001141 are updated along with this counter.  Reason for the impact: There are no radio resources available.

counter_name_alias: QUE ALL HO REQ FAIL
counter_description: Number of the rejected requests for a handover with queuing allowed.  Counter 001011 is updated along with this counter.  Reason for the impact: This may be because queuing is not allowed in the BTS, or the request is removed from the queue because of expiry of a timer, or the request is replaced by another with higher priority.

counter_name_alias: TCH ACT FAIL TARGET
counter_description: Number of TCH transactions that are ended because of a failure to activate the target channel during an SDCCH-TCH or TCH-TCH HO.  Impact: HO failure and possibly call cleared  Reason for the impact: The RRM receives the CHANNEL_ACTIVATION_NACK message.

counter_name_alias: TCH ABIS FAIL CALL
counter_description: Number of TCH transactions ended because of a failure in the Abis interface during a call in progress.  Impact: Call cleared  Reason for the impact: External / Abis Interface  The signalling problems may include missing acknowledgement of channel activation, missing indication of call establishment, receipt of an error indication, corrupted messages, missing measurement results from the BTS, excessive timing advance or some internal reasons. These failures can also contain situations when the timer T3109 expires in a BSC in call release phase while waiting for the Release Indication. The MS subscriber does not see these failures caused by the T3109 expiry as real drop calls.

counter_name_alias: TCH REQ FULL PREFERRED
counter_description: Number of TCH requests with FR preferred (both successful and unsuccessful).  Counter 001010 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: HALF TCH SEIZ SPEECH VER 2
counter_description: This counter is not in use.

counter_name_alias: FULL TCH SEIZ INT HO CH RATE
counter_description: Number of successful FR TCH seizures for an internal HO when the channel rate changes.  Counters 001008 and 001106 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: HALF TCH SEIZ INT HO CH RATE
counter_description: Number of successful HR TCH seizures for an internal HO when the channel rate changes.  Counters 001008 and 001107 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: ENDED DUE TRANSC FR RATE 2
counter_description: Number of radio TCH transactions that are ended because of a transcoder failure when speech FR version 2 is in use.

counter_name_alias: ENDED DUE TRANSC FR RATE 3
counter_description: Number of radio TCH transactions that are ended because of a transcoder failure when speech FR version 3 is in use.

counter_name_alias: ENDED DUE TRANSC HR RATE 1
counter_description: Number of radio TCH transactions that are ended because of a transcoder failure when speech HR version 1 is in use.

counter_name_alias: ENDED DUE TRANSC HR RATE 2
counter_description: Number of radio TCH transactions that are ended because of a transcoder failure when speech HR version 2 is in use.

counter_name_alias: ENDED DUE TRANSC HR RATE 3
counter_description: Number of radio TCH transactions that are ended because of a transcoder failure when speech HR version 3 is in use.

counter_name_alias: HALF TCH TR FAIL
counter_description: Total number of HR TCH transaction failures.

counter_name_alias: TCH SEIZ ATT FOR MTC
counter_description: Number of TCH seizure attempts during an MTC, in call setup phase before connection acknowledgement. In case of an external handover and handovers after external handover this counter is not incremented. In case of an intra-cell or inter-cell (TCH to TCH or SDCCH to TCH) handover this counter is updated.  Counter 001010 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: HSCSD SUCC TCH SEIZ FOR HO
counter_description: Number of successful HSCSD TCH seizures for a HO.  Counter 001008 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: SUCCESS TCH SEIZURE FOR DIRECT ACCESS
counter_description: Number of successful seizures for a TCH in direct accesses to a super-reuse TRX during the call setup phase.  Counters 001009 and 001091 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: SUCCESSFUL AMR CODEC SET DOWNGRADES
counter_description: Number of successful AMR codec set downgrades during internal HOs for the source side AMR codec set. Downgrade is made to align the source side AMR codec set with the one chosen for the target side in order to utilize the one-way downlink speech path connection for the target side during the internal HO. The utilization of one-way downlink speech path connection decreases the amount of muting experienced in the speech path connection. Downgrade decision during internal HO depends on the parameter AMR codec mode set downgrades and upgrades enabled.

counter_name_alias: SUCCESSFUL AMR CODEC SET UPGRADES
counter_description: Number of successful AMR codec set upgrades after internal HOs for the target side AMR codec set. Upgrade is made to utilize the original AMR codec set of the target BTS which set was not chosen for the target side because of target side alignment with the source side during internal HO. This alignment is made in order to utilize the one-way downlink speech path connection for the target side during the internal HO. The utilization of one-way speech path downlink connection decreases the amount of muting experienced in the speech path connection. Upgrade decision after internal HO depends on the parameters AMR codec mode set downgrades and upgrades enabled and  AMR multirate configuration in handovers.

counter_name_alias: TCH REL BSC BSC CONFLICT TARG
counter_description: Number of TCH releases because of a BSC-BSC conflict.

counter_name_alias: GPRS TER UG FROM CSW PARTIAL
counter_description: Number of territory upgrade requests from the CSW RRM to the PCU that have been served with less radio time slots than requested, i.e. partially successful PSW territory upgrade in the PCU.  Dependencies: 001213

counter_name_alias: SDCCH DROP LU EXCLUDED
counter_description: Number of dropped SDCCH without LU after SDCCH is successfully assigned.  This counter does not include phase 1 (before ESTABLISH INDICATION on SDCCH) and phase 4 (SDCCH release phase). Also the cases where call is dropped on SDCCH channel because of ASSIGNMENT FAILURE are excluded.

counter_name_alias: TCH REQUESTS FOR CALL ATTEMPT CLASS 1
counter_description: Number of TCH channel requests for a call from class 1 subscribers.

counter_name_alias: DR TRAU DOWNGRADE ATTEMPTED IN AMR HO
counter_description: Number of intra-BSC AMR FR to AMR HR handovers where the TRAU mode is attempted to be changed from FR to DR TRAU mode before handover.

counter_name_alias: TCH REQUEST WITHIN DL RX LEVEL WINDOW
counter_description: Number of TCH requests with DL RX level being within DL RX level window. All TCH requests (call setups and handovers) having DL RX level within DL RX level window are included. DL RX level measurement is never present in external handover requests, so external handovers are not visible in this counter.

counter_name_alias: DHR MULTIPLEXING FAILURE DUE TO OTHER REASON
counter_description: Number of times double half rate multiplexing is rejected because the state of the call is unsuitable or the licence capacity limit has been reached.

counter_name_alias: TRAU UPGRADE ATTEMPTED IN DFR DEMULTIPLEXING
counter_description: Number of DFR demultiplexing, neighbour OSC sub channel handover and, neighbour OSC sub channel release procedures where TRAU mode is attempted to be changed from 8k TRAU to 16k TRAU mode in source channel after the procedure.

counter_name_alias: DFR MULTIPLEXING FAILURE DUE TO TCH RESOURCE
counter_description: Number of times a suitable pair of AMR FR calls for double full rate multiplexing cannot be found.

counter_name_alias: DFR MULTIPLEXING FAILURE DUE TO CSDAP RESOURCE
counter_description: double full rate multiplexing has triggerred but CSDAP resource allocation fails because of  CSDAP congestion,   CSDAP being out of order due to failure,  CSDAP hunting timer expiry or CSDAP hunting error.

counter_name_alias: TCH ACTIVATION RETRIES DUE TO BTS OVERLOAD
counter_description: The number of TCH activation retries for call setups due to BTS overload.

counter_name_alias: DFCA ATTEMPTS WITH SMART BCCH ALLOCATION TRIGGERED BY LOAD
counter_description: Number of TCH requests received while the traffic load on the BCCH frequency band of the segment is at least on the level defined by the Smart BCCH Allocation Load Threshold parameter.

counter_name_alias: CALL LENGTH IN SMART BCCH ALLOCATION
counter_description: Combined length of DFCA TCH connections using a frequency hopping list of BCCH frequencies. Counter 001327 is updated along with this counter which maintains the number of Smart BCCH Allocation connections.

counter_name_alias: AVE AVAILABLE FULL RATE TCH
counter_description: Average number of the FR radio TCHs available. The average value is calculated by dividing the value of this counter by the value of the next counter.  Counter 002003 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AVE IDLE HALF RATE TCH BAND 4
counter_description: Average number of the idle HR TCHs per interference band (band 4). The average value is calculated by dividing the value of this counter by the value of the next counter.  Counter 002023 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AVE HSCSD USERS
counter_description: Average number of the HSCSD users.  Counter 002058 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AVE AVAIL TCH TIMESLOT
counter_description: Average number of available TCHs. The average value is calculated by dividing the value of this counter by the value of the next counter.  Counter 002060 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AVE GPRS CHANNELS
counter_description: Average number of radio time slots delivered for GPRS use. The average value is calculated by dividing the value of this counter by the  value of the next counter. The counter value does not indicate how many time slots has actually been used for GPRS traffic.   Counter 002062 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AVE PERMANENT GPRS CH
counter_description: Average number of radio time slots delivered for dedicated GPRS use. The average value is calculated by dividing the value of this counter by the value of the next counter.  Counter 002065 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AVE ADD GPRS CH HOLD TIME
counter_description: The mean holding time of additional GPRS radio TSLs (the unit of the value is 10 ms). The average value is calculated by dividing the value of this counter by the value of the next counter. Additional GPRS TSL means a TSL in GPRS use beyond the operator defined default GPRS territory.  Counter 002068 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AVE TCH TSL LOCKED POWER DOWN
counter_description: The sum of TCH timeslots in state 'BL-PWS TRX blocked for power save' .The average value is calculated by dividing the value of this counter by the value of one of the DENOMINATOR counter.

counter_name_alias: BCCH UPTIME
counter_description: Number of seconds the cell has an active BCCH and the alarm 7767 BCCH MISSING is not active.

counter_name_alias: IMMEDIATE ASSIGNMENT REJECT MESSAGES SENT TO BTS
counter_description: Number of IMMEDIATE_ASSIGNMENT_REJECT messages sent to the BTS.

counter_name_alias: DELETE IND MESSAGES RECEIVED FROM BTS
counter_description: Number of DELETE_INDICATION messages received from the BTS. BTS sends DELETE INDICATION message each time when IMMEDIATE ASSIGNMENT or IMMEDIATE ASSIGNMENT REJECT message is deleted in BTS. One IMMEDIATE ASSIGNMENT REJECT can contain reject up to four MSs. Deletion happens when there is no room for the message in access grant buffer.

counter_name_alias: GHOST CCCH RES
counter_description: Number of ghost reservations on a CCCH.  See also counter 003031.

counter_name_alias: REJ SEIZ ATT DUE DIST
counter_description: Number of seizure attempts rejected due to distance.  Counter 003030 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: IMSI DETACH TCH
counter_description: Number of successful seizures of TCHs for IMSI detach in FACCH call setup due to SDCCH congestion. If the FACCH call setup is turned off, then the counter value is zero.

counter_name_alias: AVE PAGING BUFFER CAPA
counter_description: The sum of the average paging buffer occupancy percentages. Each time a CCCH load reporting period ends, the occupancy percentage is calculated and reported in a CCCH LOAD INDICATION message. The average is calculated with (100*N)/N(max)%, where N is the occupied buffer space and N(max) is the maximum buffer space during the CCCH load reporting period.   The CCCH load reporting period is the time between CCCH LOAD INDICATION message sendings. This counter stores the sum of the average paging buffer values received in CCCH LOAD INDICATION messages.   Counter 003037 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AVE PAGING LOAD AIR
counter_description: Average paging load on CCCH indicated by radio block occupancy for paging messages.  Radio Block Occupancy carries information on the Radio interface load in percents of the associated CCCH timeslot. The radio block occupancy percentage for AGCH messages requiring DRX (occupied radio blocks vs. all radio blocks during reporting period) is calculated and reported in CCCH_LOAD_ IND message.  Counter 003052 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: PEO NBR PS PAGE DROPS AT BTS
counter_description: PEO PS Paging Drops Counter indicated in CCCH LOAD INDICATION message.

counter_name_alias: MSC I SUCCESS HO
counter_description: Number of successful incoming HOs controlled by the MSC.  Dependencies: When one of the counters 004043, 004044 or 004045 is updated. This counter represents their sum.

counter_name_alias: BSC I UNSUCCESS HO DUE CONN
counter_description: Number of incoming HOs, controlled by the BSC, that are unsuccessful due to a connection failure (the MS fails to move to the target channel).  Impact: - HO failure - The call may possibly be cleared  Reason for the impact: External/Abis interface  Dependencies: a) Counter 004015 is updated along with this counter. b) Counters 004016, 004083 and 004084 are updated along with this counter. c) Counter 004016 or 004042 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: INT CELL UNSUCCESS HO DUE MOVE
counter_description: Number of intra-cell HOs that are unsuccessful because the MS cannot either move to the target channel or return to the source channel.  Counter 004085 is updated along with this counter.  Impact: Call cleared  Reason for the impact: External/Abis interface

counter_name_alias: CAUSE DOWNLINK LEVEL
counter_description: Number of HO attempts caused by downlink level (outgoing).

counter_name_alias: CAUSE DISTANCE
counter_description: Number of HO attempts caused by distance (outgoing).

counter_name_alias: MSC O SDCCH TCH
counter_description: Number of successful outgoing SDCCH to TCH HOs controlled by the MSC.

counter_name_alias: MSC O SDCCH
counter_description: Number of successful outgoing SDCCH to SDCCH HOs controlled by the MSC.

counter_name_alias: MSC O TCH TCH AT
counter_description: Number of attempts to outgoing TCH to TCH HOs controlled by the MSC.

counter_name_alias: MSC O SDCCH TCH AT
counter_description: Number of attempts to outgoing SDCCH to TCH HOs controlled by the MSC.

counter_name_alias: MSC O SDCCH AT
counter_description: Number of attempts to outgoing SDCCH to SDCCH HOs controlled by the MSC.

counter_name_alias: MSC O FAIL LACK
counter_description: Number of outgoing HOs, controlled by the MSC, that are unsuccessful because there are no radio resources available in the target cell.  Impact: HO failure  Reason for the impact: Internal

counter_name_alias: BSC O NONOPT AT
counter_description: Number of attempts to outgoing HOs to a non-optimum cell controlled by the BSC.

counter_name_alias: CAUSE DIR RETRY
counter_description: Number of HO attempts due to directed retry.

counter_name_alias: MSC I END OF HO
counter_description: Number of end of handover procedures in incoming HOs that are controlled by the MSC.  Dependency: b) Counter 004108 is updated along with this counter.  Impact: - HO failure - Possibly call cleared  Reason for the impact: External/Abis interface

counter_name_alias: BSC O DROP CALLS
counter_description: Number of calls that are dropped during outgoing HOs controlled by the BSC.  Dependencies: a) Counters 004012, 004016 and 004083 are updated along with this counter. b) Counters 004013, 004017 and 004083 are updated along with this counter.  Impact: Call cleared

counter_name_alias: CAUSE FIELD DROP
counter_description: Number of HO attempts caused due to rapid field drop and High Speed Rail HO.

counter_name_alias: CAUSE LOW DISTANCE
counter_description: Number of HO attempts caused by low distance.

counter_name_alias: HO ATT DUE ERFD
counter_description: Number of inter-cell HO attempts during an ERFD (Enhanced Rapid Field Drop) HO. All inter-cell HOs during ERFD HO are mapped to the ERFD HO counter.

counter_name_alias: HO ATTEMPT INTER BAND SDCCH
counter_description: Number of attempts to perform an SDCCH-SDCCH handover, based on the duration of an SDCCH reservation, from a BTS on the BCCH frequency band to a BTS on another frequency band of the segment.  Information on the success of the attempts can be seen on BSC level in counter 051136.

counter_name_alias: INTRA CELL SUCCESS TCH HO BETWEEN BANDS
counter_description: Number of completed and successful TCH to TCH handovers between two BTSs on different frequency bands of a segment. PGSM 900 and EGSM 900 are regarded as parts of the same GSM 900 frequency band.  Counter 004132 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: HO ATT DUE TO HSCSD
counter_description: Number of intra cell handover attempts that are made due to the HSCSD traffic.

counter_name_alias: SUCCESSFUL HO INTER BAND TCH
counter_description: Number of successful and completed TCH-TCH handovers between BTSs of different frequency bands of a segment due to load.  Counter 004135 is updated in the source BTS of the handover.

counter_name_alias: HO ATTEMPT DUE TO INTER SYSTEM DIRECT ACCESS
counter_description: Number of attempts to perform an SDCCH-TCH handover from the GSM to the WCDMA RAN due to Direct Access.  The success of the attempts can be seen on the BSC level in counter 051154 (EXT OUT INTER SYSTEM DIRECT ACCESS) of the BSC Level Clear Code (PM) Measurement.

counter_name_alias: INTRA CELL TCH HO TO EXTERNAL SUCCESSFUL
counter_description: Number of successful incoming external handovers that originally were BSC-controlled internal intra-cell TCH-TCH handovers but were changed to MSC controlled due to pool switching or avoiding DL muting when speech coding was changed.

counter_name_alias: HO FROM SUPER EXTENDED TO EXTENDED AREA SUCCESSFUL
counter_description: Number of successful intra-cell handovers from the super-extended area to the extended area.

counter_name_alias: HO ATTEMPT FROM DHR DUE TO UL RX LEVEL DIFFERENCE
counter_description: Number of demultiplexing HO attempts starting from a double half rate TCH based on UL Rx level difference between the multiplexed double half rate TCHs.

counter_name_alias: HO ATTEMPT FROM DHR DUE TO RX LEVEL
counter_description: Number of demultiplexing handover attempts starting from a double half rate TCH based on Rx level.

counter_name_alias: HO ATTEMPT FROM AMR FR TO DFR
counter_description: Number of handover attempts from an AMR FR TCH to a double full rate TCH.

counter_name_alias: HO FROM AMR FR TO DFR SUCCESSFUL
counter_description: Number of successful handovers from an AMR FR TCH to a double full rate TCH.

counter_name_alias: HO FROM DFR TO DFR IN 8K TRAU MODE SUCCESSFUL
counter_description: Number of successful remultiplexing handovers from a DFR TCH to a DFR TCH in 8kbit/s TRAU mode.

counter_name_alias: HO ATTEMPT FROM NOB DUE TO INTERFERENCE BETWEEN RANS
counter_description: Number of intra-cell handover attempts from Nearest Offset BTS (NOB) resources due to too high or too low DL Rx level.   When the DL Rx level is high, there is a risk that GSM system causes interference to another Radio Access Network (WCDMA/LTE). When DL Rx level is low, there is a risk that another Radio Access Network causes interference to GSM system.

counter_name_alias: HO FROM WB AMR TO FR
counter_description: Number of incoming handovers involving codec change from Wideband AMR to Normal FR.

counter_name_alias: HO FROM AMR HR TO WB AMR
counter_description: Number of incoming handovers involving codec change from AMR HR to Wideband AMR.

counter_name_alias: AVE BS POWER
counter_description: Sum of TRX specific downlink RF power level value samples in the serving cell. The value range of a single RF power level sample is 0...15.   RF power level value mapping (Pmax is the maximum transmission power of the BTS):  0 -> Pmax - 0 dBm  1 -> Pmax - 2 dBm  2 -> Pmax - 4 dBm  ...  15 -> Pmax - 30 dBm.   If Pmax is 43 dBm, then the value 0 means 43 dBm and the value 15 means 13 dBm.   The average TRX specific downlink RF power level used in the cell can be calculated by dividing this counter with the denominator counter 005007 POWER DENOMINATOR 2.

counter_name_alias: PW ID OF FREQUENCY GROUP
counter_description: Identification of the frequency group where the TRX belongs to.

counter_name_alias: MS POWER INCREASE BY SIGNAL QUAL WITH 14.4  DATA
counter_description: Number of MS power control increase commands in a cell, caused by the uplink signal quality in 14.4 kbit/s data connection.  This counter contains MS power control messages where the new commanded RF power level is higher than the RF power level the MS is currently using while the connection type is 14.4 kbit/s data.

counter_name_alias: TRANSM ABORT
counter_description: Number of the frames received with transmission aborted.

counter_name_alias: REJ FRM TRANS
counter_description: Number of the rejected frames transmitted.

counter_name_alias: T1 EXPIRATIONS
counter_description: Timer T1 specifies the time limit in which the remote end of the connection must acknowledge the receipt of the frame. If this timer expires, the frame is transmitted again.

counter_name_alias: REC CL PCTS2
counter_description: Number of the clear packets received; cause > 0.

counter_name_alias: REC RNR PCTS
counter_description: Number of the RNR packets received.

counter_name_alias: TRANS RST PCTS
counter_description: Number of the reset packets transmitted.

counter_name_alias: TRANS CL PCTS
counter_description: Number of the clear packets transmitted.

counter_name_alias: TRANS RESTART PCTS
counter_description: Number of the restart packets transmitted.

counter_name_alias: TRANS RNR PCTS
counter_description: Number of the RNR packets transmitted.

counter_name_alias: T21 EXPIRATIONS
counter_description: Number of the time-outs of timer T21.

counter_name_alias: T22 EXPIRATIONS
counter_description: Number of the time-outs of timer T22.

counter_name_alias: REC DATA PCTS
counter_description: Number of the data packets received.

counter_name_alias: REC DATA PCTS DIS
counter_description: Number of the data packets received and discarded.

counter_name_alias: REC DATA SEGM
counter_description: Number of the data segments received.

counter_name_alias: TRANS DATA PCTS
counter_description: Number of the data packets transmitted.

counter_name_alias: TRANS DATA SEGM
counter_description: Number of the data segments transmitted.

counter_name_alias: SUCC INC CALLS
counter_description: Number of the successful incoming calls.

counter_name_alias: SUCC OUT CALLS
counter_description: Number of the successful outgoing calls.

counter_name_alias: UNSUCC INC CALLS
counter_description: Number of the unsuccessful incoming calls.

counter_name_alias: UNSUCC OUT CALLS
counter_description: Number of the unsuccessful outgoing calls.

counter_name_alias: CALLS DUR A
counter_description: Number of the calls with duration A; 0 < A < 10.

counter_name_alias: CALLS DUR B
counter_description: Number of the calls with duration B; 10 < B < 300.

counter_name_alias: OUT CALLS REJ
counter_description: Number of the outgoing calls rejected.

counter_name_alias: FREQ DL QUAL 5
counter_description: Number of samples with downlink RX quality within class 5.

counter_name_alias: AMR FR CODEC MODE 1 ON UPLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 0
counter_description: Number of AMR FR codec mode 1 usage on uplink direction within RxQual 0. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.  Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR FR CODEC MODE 1 ON DOWNLINK DIRECTION WITH RX QUAL 0
counter_description: Number of AMR FR codec mode 1 usage on downlink direction within RxQual 0. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.  Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR FR CODEC MODE 1 ON UPLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 5
counter_description: Number of AMR FR codec mode 1 usage on uplink direction within RxQual 5. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.  Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR FR CODEC MODE 1 ON DOWNLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 7
counter_description: Number of AMR FR codec mode 1 usage on downlink direction within RxQual 7. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.  Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR FR CODEC MODE 2 ON UPLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 6
counter_description: Number of AMR FR codec mode 2 usage on uplink direction within RxQual 6. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.  Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR FR CODEC MODE 3 ON DOWNLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 4
counter_description: Number of AMR FR codec mode 3 usage on downlink direction within RxQual 4. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.  Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR FR CODEC MODE 4 ON UPLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 3
counter_description: Number of AMR FR codec mode 4 usage on uplink direction within RxQual 3. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.  Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 1 ON UPLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 0
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 1 usage on uplink direction within RxQual 0. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 1 ON DOWNLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 1
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 1 usage on downlink direction within RxQual 1. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 1 ON DOWNLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 2
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 1 usage on downlink direction within RxQual 2. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 2 ON UPLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 0
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 2 usage on uplink direction within RxQual 0. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 2 ON UPLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 1
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 2 usage on uplink direction within RxQual 1. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 2 ON DOWNLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 6
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 2 usage on downlink direction within RxQual 6. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 2 ON DOWNLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 7
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 2 usage on downlink direction within RxQual 7. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 3 ON UPLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 5
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 3 usage on uplink direction within RxQual 5. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 3 ON UPLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 6
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 3 usage on uplink direction within RxQual 6. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: AMR HR CODEC MODE 4 ON DOWNLINK DIRECTION WITH RXQUAL 3
counter_description: Number of AMR HR codec mode 4 usage on downlink direction within RxQual 3. On fast link adaptation (LA) mode the codec mode is the last codec mode used during the radio link measurement interval. On slow LA mode this counter indicates the only used codec mode on the radio link measurement interval.   Counter 014149 AMR CODEC MODE SETS is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: SAIC FREQ DL QUAL 0
counter_description: Number of samples with downlink RX quality within class 0 for SAIC.

counter_name_alias: EXTERNAL HO SOURCE FAILURES
counter_description: Number of failures during external handover signalling on the source SDCCH or TCH.  Impact: Call cleared

counter_name_alias: ATT LOCATION UPDATE
counter_description: Number of location update attempts (DX cause number: 4).

counter_name_alias: LOCATION UPDATE
counter_description: Number of successful location updates (DX cause number: 10).

counter_name_alias: FACCH IMSI DETACH
counter_description: Number of successful FACCH calls with establishment cause imsi detach (DX cause number: 27).

counter_name_alias: FACCH EMERGENCY CALL
counter_description: Number of successful FACCH calls with establishment cause emergency call (DX cause number: 20).

counter_name_alias: ESTAB EXT IN DISTANCE
counter_description: Number of successful incoming external handovers that are established with BSSMAP cause distance (DX cause number: 84).

counter_name_alias: EXT IN SWITCH CRC POOL
counter_description: Number of incoming external handover attempts that are made in order to change the circuit pool in the A interface (DX cause number: 90). NOTE! The source BSC is the same as the target BSC.  Counters 051012 and 057009 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: EXT IN BSC TRHO
counter_description: Number of successful incoming external handovers that are set up with BSSMAP cause traffic (DX cause number 92).  Counters 051012 and 057009 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: EXT OUT SWITCH CRC POOL
counter_description: Number of outgoing external handover attempts that are made in order to change the circuit pool in the A interface (DX cause number: 116). NOTE! The source BSC is the same as the target BSC.  Counters 051011 and 057010 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: EXT OUT DET SLOW MOV MS
counter_description: Number of successful outgoing external handovers that are made because it is detected that the MS is moving slowly (DX cause number: 118). The MS is handed over to a lower layer cell, for example, from a macro cell to a micro cell. The slow speed detection is based on MS speed indications sent by the BTS.   Counters 051011 and 057010 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: INTER SLOW MOVING MS
counter_description: Number of internal inter-cell handovers that are set up with DX cause Slow Moving MS in Macro Cell (DX cause number: 138). The slow speed detection is based on the received measurement of adjacent micro cells and on the umbrella-like handover criteria.  Counters 051013 and 057012 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: INTER DET FAST MOV MS
counter_description: Number of successful internal inter-cell handovers that are made because it is detected that the MS is moving fast (DX cause number: 156). The MS is handed over to a upper layer cell, for example, from a micro cell to a macro cell. The fast speed detection is based on the MS speed indications sent by the BTS.   Counters 051013 and 057012 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: PS PAG REF DUE BCSU30 BIGLOAD
counter_description: Number of rejected PS paging messages inside the BCSU/BCXU.

counter_name_alias: PS PAG REF DUE BCSU36 BIGLOAD
counter_description: Number of rejected PS paging messages inside the BCSU/BCXU.

counter_name_alias: PAG FROM A INT REF DUE BCSU31
counter_description: Number of paging messages from A-interface that are rejected inside the BCSU/BCXU.

counter_name_alias: INTRA DTM MT CS TO PS TERRITORY HO
counter_description: Number of successful internal intra-cell handovers started as part of a mobile-terminated DTM call establishment (DX cause number: 171). A CS-connection handover from the CS territory to the PS territory is performed.  Counters 051014 and 057013 are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: ESTABLISHED INCOMING EXTERNAL DTM HO DUE NO RESOURCES
counter_description: Number of successful incoming external handovers due to the reason that there are no free PS resources available for a DTM call or DTM call reallocation in the source cell. The handover is established with BSSMAP cause traffic load (DX cause number: 95).   Counter 004195 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: INTRA HO FROM LRTCH TO NORMAL AREA
counter_description: Number of successful intra-cell HOs from Long Reach TCH to normal area.

counter_name_alias: INTRA HO FROM EXTENDED TO SUPER EXTENDED AREA
counter_description: Number of successful internal intra-cell handovers from the extended area to the super-extended area (DX cause number: 177).   Counters 004230 HO FROM EXTENDED TO SUPER EXTENDED AREA SUCCESSFUL, 051014 INTERNAL INTRA HO SUCC and 057013 INT INTRA HO SUCCESS are updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: CELL BROADCAST REQUEST
counter_description: The number of BTSs for which Cell Broadcast message activations are requested.

counter_name_alias: INTRA HO FROM NOB
counter_description: Number of successful BSC internal intra-cell handovers from Nearest Offset BTS (NOB) resources due to too high or too low Rx level.  When the DL Rx level is too high, there is a risk that GSM system causes interference to another Radio Access Network (WCDMA/LTE). When DL Rx level is too low, there is a risk that another Radio Access Network causes interference to GSM system.

counter_name_alias: SUCC TCH SEIZURES
counter_description: Number of TCH seizures.

counter_name_alias: INTERF OF CELL 1
counter_description: High measured interference caused by the interfering cell 1.

counter_name_alias: INTERF OF CELL 2
counter_description: High measured interference caused by the interfering cell 2.

counter_name_alias: HO SUCC TO REG FR
counter_description: Number of successful HOs from a super-reuse TRX to a regular TRX.

counter_name_alias: UO DR ATT TO SUPER
counter_description: Number of assignment/HO attempts from SDCCH to super-reuse frequencies.

counter_name_alias: EXT HO TARGET FAILURE
counter_description: Number of the handover failures during external HO target signalling on SDCCH or TCH. The call can continue on the old channel.  If the call is cleared, counter 057004 is updated on the source BSC.  Impact: HO failure. Call is possibly cleared

counter_name_alias: TCH RE EST ASSIGN
counter_description: Number of the TCH re-establishment assignments.

counter_name_alias: CIPHERING MODE A5/0 USAGE
counter_description: Number of times ciphering mode A5/0 used.

counter_name_alias: SAMPLES IN SPEED CLASS 2
counter_description: Number of samples in speed class 2.

counter_name_alias: TCH RESRV BY SINGLE BAND
counter_description: Number of TCH reservations made by single band subscribers.

counter_name_alias: CI BSIC DECODE TIME
counter_description: BSIC decode time indicates the period starting from call setup or handover during which the C/I ratio is not calculated. The unit is 0.48s, that is, time is multiplies of 0.48 s.

counter_name_alias: INTERF UPLINK CI RATIO
counter_description: Number of times when the estimated uplink C/I ratio of the test cell is within the observed C/I band and the interference is caused by ongoing calls in the interfering cell.  This counter is updated with counter 060014.

counter_name_alias: ERRORED SECONDS
counter_description: The errored seconds.

counter_name_alias: DEGRADED MINUTES
counter_description: The degraded minutes.

counter_name_alias: INCOMING SIGNAL MISSING CLASS 4
counter_description: The total number of missing incoming signals, class 4.

counter_name_alias: AVAILABLE TIME FOR REMOTE END
counter_description: The time when the connection has been available.  Counters 065007-065009 help detect smaller disturbances in the connection. Note that those counters are more frequently updated than this counter.

counter_name_alias: FRAME ALIGN LOST CLASS 3
counter_description: The total number of lost frame alignments, class 3.

counter_name_alias: MULTI TCH REQ REJ FOR HSCSD
counter_description: Number of the rejected multislot requests due to lack of resources for an HSCSD connection. No channels are allocated.  The counter is not updated if, for example, four channels are requested, but only two allocated.  Impact: Possible call clear

counter_name_alias: ONE TCH SEIZ TIME FOR 14.4
counter_description: Allocated time for a one-channel HSCSD connection with 14.4 coding.

counter_name_alias: ERRORED SECONDS
counter_description: The errored seconds (ES).

counter_name_alias: RF INPUT LEVEL MAX
counter_description: The minimum input level received during observation period. Where 0 means -100dBm.( 88 means -12dBm, for example).

counter_name_alias: TOTAL TIME
counter_description: The time passed during the counters have been updated.

counter_name_alias: RF INPUT LEVEL MIN
counter_description: The minimum input level received during observation period.Where 0 means -100dBm.( 88 means -12dBm, for example).

counter_name_alias: TCH RESERV BY MULTISLOT INCAPABLE MS
counter_description: Number of TCH reservations made by a multislot incapable MS.

counter_name_alias: TCH RESERV BY MSLOT CL 3 MS
counter_description: Number of TCH reservations made by a multislot class 3 supporting MS.

counter_name_alias: TCH RESERV BY MSLOT CL 18 MS
counter_description: Number of TCH reservations made by a multislot class 18 supporting MS.

counter_name_alias: AVE DUR UL TBF
counter_description: The sum of normally released uplink TBF durations. The average duration per segment is achieved when this counter is divided by counter 072004 AVE DUR UL TBF DEN.

counter_name_alias: UL TBF WITH RETRY BIT SET
counter_description: The number of established uplink TBFs with the Retry Bit set to 1. The Retry Bit (R) indicates whether the MS has transmitted the CHANNEL_REQUEST message, the PACKET_CHANNEL_REQUEST message or the EGPRS_PACKET_CHANNEL_REQUEST message once or more than once during its most recent channel access. The MS sends the same value from the R bit in each uplink RLC/MAC block of the TBF.

counter_name_alias: MAX UL LLC PER TBF
counter_description: The maximum number of uplink LLCs per normally released TBFs. The LLC frames are sent between the MS and SGSN.

counter_name_alias: MAX DL LLC PER TBF
counter_description: The maximum number of downlink LLCs per normally released TBFs.

counter_name_alias: UL TBF REALLOC DUE SIM DL TBF
counter_description: The number of successful uplink TBF reallocations due to an establishment of simultaneous downlink TBFs. For example, the number of UL TSLs is decreased when simultaneous DL TBFs are established, or when better resources are made available for the UL TBF. When an uplink TBF already exists and a downlink TBF is established, the uplink TBF may be reallocated and the value of this counter increases.

counter_name_alias: RLC DATA BLOCKS DL CS1
counter_description: The number of new RLC data blocks in downlink with CS1. This counter does not count the retransmitted data blocks.

counter_name_alias: DISC LLC BLOCKS DUE TO EXP
counter_description: The number of discarded LLC PDUs because of expired lifetime.

counter_name_alias: NBR OF DL TBF ESTABLISHMENT FAILED
counter_description: The number of downlink GPRS TBF establishments that have failed due to no response from MS. This counter does not consider EGPRS TBFs.

counter_name_alias: AVER TBFS PER TSL UL
counter_description: The sum of uplink TBFs' average values per timeslot.  An average value is counted once per second from all the timeslots of a GPRS/EDGE territory, including timeslots with no TBFs. The obtained decimal value is then multiplied by 100 and summed up to this counter.

counter_name_alias: NUM OF LLC DATA BYTES RECEIVED FROM SGSN
counter_description: The number of LLC DATA bytes received from SGSN specific to a BTS. This will aid in computing BTS level DL TPUT calculation.

counter_name_alias: VOLUME WEIGHTED LLC THROUGHPUT EDGE 4 DL NUMERATOR
counter_description: The numerator for downlink Volume Weighted (VW) LLC throughput in EDGE mode, for MSs which are capable of four or more TSLs in downlink allocation. Longer data bursts are weighted more than short bursts. The counter contains the sum of the throughputs weighted by the volume of each LLC transmission burst within the TBF. An LLC transmission burst is a transmission period between two transmission breaks. The unit of the counter is 100 bytes^2/10 ms. Average VW throughput in EDGE mode is achieved by dividing 072109 by 072110.   In DTM mode this counter is updated if the DTM multi-slot class allows to allocate four or more TSLs for the DTM PS connection.  Counter 072110 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: VOLUME WEIGHTED LLC THROUGHPUT EDGE 4 DL DENOMINATOR
counter_description: The denominator for Volume Weighted (VW) LLC throughput in EDGE mode, for MSs which are capable of four or more TSLs in downlink allocation. The counter contains all the bytes transmitted within TBFs. Average VW throughput in EDGE mode is achieved by dividing 072109 by 072110.   In DTM mode this counter is updated if the DTM multi-slot class allows to allocate four or more TSLs for the DTM PS connection.  Counter 072109 is updated along with this counter.

counter_name_alias: UL DATA CONT AFTER COUNTDOWN
counter_description: Shows how many times mobile stations use the Extended UL TBF mode to send new data on the same TBF.

counter_name_alias: UL GPRS TBF FOR EGPRS REQ
counter_description: The number of GPRS TBF allocations done for EGPRS request in GPRS territory because of congestion in EGPRS area.

counter_name_alias: ALLOC 8 TSL UL
counter_description: The number of allocations for eight TSLs in UL TBF allocation or reallocation.

counter_name_alias: REQ 2 TSL UL FOR EGPRS MS
counter_description: The number of requests for two TSLs in UL EGPRS TBF allocation.   Counters 072034-072037, 072125-072128 REQ 1-8 TSL UL also contain EGPRS requests.

counter_name_alias: OUT DL TBF DUE REALLOC
counter_description: The number of outgoing downlink TBFs because of reallocation (TBF is moved from BTS to another in same segment).

counter_name_alias: EGPRS UL CTRL BLOCKS
counter_description: The number of RLC/MAC control blocks received from MS with EGPRS TBF.   Counter 072076: RLC/MAC UL control blocks also includes EGPRS ctrl blocks.

counter_name_alias: RETRA DATA BLOCKS UL CS2
counter_description: The number of retransmitted uplink RLC blocks using coding scheme 2 (CS2).

counter_name_alias: DL TBF DATA ATTEMPTS
counter_description: Number of downlink TBF establishments for data transfer. The establishment cause is determined from the T bit of the QoS information element in the first DL-UNITDATA PDU.

counter_name_alias: WEIGHTED DL TSL ALLOC EDGE DENOMINATOR
counter_description: The denominator for weighted downlink allocation for all EDGE TBFs and all MS classes. The counter contains the sum of downlink allocation durations. Abnormal releases are not included. Average allocation is achieved by dividing 072193 by 072194.

counter_name_alias: DA TO EDA REALLOCATIONS
counter_description: The number of DA to EDA reallocations. The reasons for reallocating DA to EDA can be either MS EDA capability becomes known or According to the capacity estimation, EDA offers better capacity than DA

counter_name_alias: PACKET PAGING REQUEST FOR CS PAGING NMO II
counter_description: Number of PACKET PAGING REQUEST messages sent on the PACCH channel for CS paging in NMO II mode.

counter_name_alias: SMART PHONE 1 TSL DL TBF ESTABLISHED
counter_description: Number of (E)GPRS DL TBFs established in singleslot configuration due to the Smart Resource Adaptation feature

counter_name_alias: DLDC ATTEMPT FAILED DUE TERRITORY
counter_description: Number of failed DLDC allocation requests due to lacking DLDC territory in DLDC enabled BTS.

counter_name_alias: MCS DIFFERENCE BETWEEN TWO TRXS DENOMINATOR
counter_description: Number of times MCS difference between two TRXs is evaluated. Incremented by one any time when MCS difference between two TRXs is evaluated, irrespective of the difference (commanded MCSs may be different or same).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 1 KBYTES REC FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 1: Number of kilobytes in the received frames.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074011 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 3 SENT FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 3: Number of sent frames.   The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074011 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 3 BYTES DISC SENT FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 3: Number of bytes in the discarded sent frames.   The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074011 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 4 STAT ACT TO INACT
counter_description: DLCI 4: Number of the DLCI status changes from active to inactive.   The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074011 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 5 KBYTES SENT
counter_description: DLCI 5: Number of kilobytes in the sent frames.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074059 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 6 STAT ACT TO INACT
counter_description: DLCI 6: Number of the DLCI status changes from active to inactive.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074011 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 7 DISC SENT FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 7: Number of discarded sent frames.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if counter 074083 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 9 KBYTES REC FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 9: Number of kilobytes in the received frames.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074107 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 10 KBYTES REC FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 10: Number of kilobytes in the received frames.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074119 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 11 DISC REC FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 11: Number of discarded received frames.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074131 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 13 SENT FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 13: Number of sent frames.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074155 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 13 BYTES DISC SENT FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 13: Number of bytes in the discarded sent frames.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074155 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 14 DISC REC FRMS
counter_description: DLCI 14: Number of discarded received frames.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074167 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 14 STAT ACT TO INACT
counter_description: DLCI 14: Number of the DLCI status changes from active to inactive.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074167 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: DLCI 15 STAT ACT TO INACT
counter_description: DLCI 15: Number of the DLCI status changes from active to inactive.  The value of this counter is irrelevant if the counter 074179 has a value FFFFFFFF (hex).

counter_name_alias: AVE DOWNL SIGNAL STRENGTH IN SERV CELL
counter_description: Average strength of the downlink signal received from a serving cell. The values range from 0 to 73. This counter is updated with counter 075004.

counter_name_alias: TOT NBR OF PCM STS IN EDAP UL
counter_description: Total number of 16 kbit/s PCM subtimeslots in EDAP. Sum of samples.  Dependency: 076018 DYNAMIC ABIS DENOM UL

counter_name_alias: CLASS 1 BOUNDARY
counter_description: The lower limit of FER class 1 for both uplink and downlink directions used in a measurement period. Values below this boundary are updating the class 0 counters. The default value for this limit is 20 (2%).

counter_name_alias: CLASS 2 BOUNDARY
counter_description: The lower limit of FER class 2 for both uplink and downlink directions used in a measurement period. The default value for this limit is 40 (4%).

counter_name_alias: NBR OF EST DL FER CL 5
counter_description: Number of estimated DL FER samples in class 5.

counter_name_alias: NBR OF LOC REQ EMERGENCY
counter_description: Number of emergency call related location requests received by the LCS interface.

counter_name_alias: FEATURE NOT SUPPORTED
counter_description: Number of location requests which are rejected because the requested location service is not supported.

counter_name_alias: NBR OF LOCATION CALCULATIONS CELL ID TA
counter_description: Number of location requests which are calculated in the internal SMLC with the cell ID + TA method.

counter_name_alias: NUMBER OF BAD RLC DATA BLOCKS WITH VALID HEADER UL UNACK MODE
counter_description: Number of UL RLC data blocks received in unacknowledged mode having a valid header but bad contents. In unacknowledged mode bad blocks are not retransmitted.

counter_name_alias: RETRANSMITTED RLC DATA BLOCKS UL
counter_description: Number of retransmitted UL RLC data blocks carried within radio blocks in acknowledged mode  having a valid header. These retransmitted RLC data blocks can also be sent by an EGPRS MS without request from the PCU.

counter_name_alias: TOTAL NBR OF RLC BLOCKS
counter_description: Total number of the transferred RLC blocks.

counter_name_alias: VWTHR NUMERATOR GPRS
counter_description: Numerator for Volume Weighted (VW) LLC throughput in the GPRS mode. Longer data bursts are weighted more than short bursts. The counter contains the sum of the throughputs weighted by the volume of each LLC transmission burst within the TBF. LLC transmission burst is a transmission period between two transmission breaks. All MS classes are taken into account. The unit of the counter is 100 bytes^2/10 ms. The average VW throughput in GPRS mode is achieved by dividing 090007 by 090008.

counter_name_alias: OFFSET SAMPLE OF +3
counter_description: Number of the measured offset samples of +3 dB.

counter_name_alias: OFFSET SAMPLE OF +37
counter_description: Number of the measured offset samples of +37 dB.

counter_name_alias: OFFSET SAMPLE OF -19
counter_description: Number of the measured offset samples of -19 dB.

counter_name_alias: OFFSET SAMPLE OF -12
counter_description: Number of the measured offset samples of -12 dB.

counter_name_alias: OFFSET SAMPLE OF -3
counter_description: Number of the measured offset samples of -3 dB.

counter_name_alias: PCCO TO GPRS MS DUE PWR BDGT
counter_description: The number of started NCCR procedures for GPRS mobiles due to power budget criteria.

counter_name_alias: PCCO SENT DUE COVERAGE ISNCCR
counter_description: The number of started NCCR procedures due to coverage based criteria for the inter-system NCCR depending on the WCDMA FDD NCCR. The preferred parameter coverage based NCCR is triggered as soon as an appropriate WCDMA FDD cell is available, or only in case there is not an appropriate GSM/EDGE cell available and an appropriate WCDMA FDD cell is available.

counter_name_alias: NCCR NOT STARTED DUE AC
counter_description: The number of times a new NCCR is not started because of target cell admission control.

counter_name_alias: AVE NCCR DURATION SUM
counter_description: The sum of NCCR durations. The average NCCR duration is calculated by dividing this counter by the number of received flush messages.

counter_name_alias: PFC ACTIVE TIME UL SUM
counter_description: The sum of times when data transfer for PFC (with certain TC+ARP) has been active in UL direction. Dependency: 097019 LLC BYTES UL

counter_name_alias: SPARE097031
counter_description: This counter is not in use.

counter_name_alias: NBR OF RCVD SIGNAL PACKETS
counter_description: The number of NS signals (all NS-xxxx and SNS-xxxx messages excluding NS-UNITDATA) received from the SGSN.

counter_name_alias: BA LIST CHANGED
counter_description: Identifies if the BA list is changed during the measurement period or if the process of updating the BA list of a BTS with a new MBAL is unsuccessful.  Range 0 = BA list not changed  1 = BA list changed

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+7 UL
counter_description: The number of uplink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 7 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+8 DL
counter_description: The number of downlink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 8 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+9 UL
counter_description: The number of uplink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 9 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+9 DL
counter_description: The number of downlink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 9 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+10 UL
counter_description: The number of uplink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 10 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+10 DL
counter_description: The number of downlink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 10 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+11 UL
counter_description: The number of uplink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 11 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+11 DL
counter_description: The number of downlink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 11 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+12 UL
counter_description: The number of uplink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 12 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+12 DL
counter_description: The number of downlink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I +12 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+13 UL
counter_description: The number of uplink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 13 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+13 DL
counter_description: The number of downlink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 13 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+14 UL
counter_description: The number of uplink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 14 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET+14 DL
counter_description: The number of downlink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I + 14 dB.

counter_name_alias: DFCA C/I TARGET-8 UL
counter_description: The number of uplink DFCA assignments where the C/I level equals the target C/I - 8 dB.

counter_name_alias: MOST INTERFERED C/I TARGET+4 UL
counter_description: Number of uplink DFCA estimates where the uplink C/I value of the most interfered connection equals the target C/I value + 4 dB.

counter_name_alias: MOST INTERFERED C/I TARGET+15 DL
counter_description: Number of downlink DFCA estimates where the downlink C/I value of the most interfered connection equals the target C/I value + 15 dB.

counter_name_alias: MOST INTERFERED C/I TARGET-6 UL
counter_description: Number of uplink DFCA estimates where the uplink C/I value of the most interfered connection equals the target C/I value - 6 dB.

counter_name_alias: MOST INTERFERED C/I TARGET-6 DL
counter_description: Number of downlink DFCA estimates where the downlink C/I value of the most interfered connection equals the target C/I value - 6 dB.

counter_name_alias: SUCC DFCA ASS HIGH LOAD
counter_description: The number of successful DFCA assignments in high MCMU load situation. Due to high  MCMU load, the DFCA channel search is limited and therefore the most optimal DFCA  channel cannot necessarily be allocated.

counter_name_alias: PRIMARY DFCA ALGORITHM ATT
counter_description: The number of times the DFCA Algorithm has chosen the DFCA layer to be searched before the regular layer.

counter_name_alias: WPS AVE OCCU FTCH COUNT
counter_description: The average number of full rate traffic channels occupied by WPS users during a measurement period.  To calculate the true average number of full rate traffic channels occupied by WPS users, you must divide the value of this counter by a denominator.  This counter is updated with counter 103001.

counter_name_alias: WPS PRI 3 NOT ALL QUE DUE LENG
counter_description: The number of priority level 3 WPS users that are either dropped from the queue because of the arrival of a higher priority WPS user or are not allowed into the queue because the maximum queue length has been reached.

counter_name_alias: WPS PRI 2 REM FROM QUE DUE TIM
counter_description: The number of priority level 2 WPS users that are dropped from the queue because the queuing timer has expired.

counter_name_alias: WPS PRI 3 REM FROM QUE DUE TIM
counter_description: The number of priority level 3 WPS users that are dropped from the queue because the queuing timer has expired.

counter_name_alias: IBHO ATT TO UTRAN DEFAULT ANE
counter_description: The number of IMSI-based handover attempts from the GSM to the default authorised network because of coverage of UTRAN cell of an equivalent PLMN.  The default authorised network is used for an unidentified subscriber. This means that the corresponding subscriber group could not find the subscriber.  Failure of the attempts can be seen in the counter IBHO UNS TO UTRAN DEFAULT ANE of the IBHO measurement. Corresponding handover counters in HO measurement are updated normally in addition to this counter.

counter_name_alias: IBHO UNS TO UTRAN ANE N01
counter_description: Number of unsuccessful IMSI-based handovers from the GSM to the UTRAN authorised network.  Attempts can be seen in the counter IBHO ATT TO UTRAN ANE N01 of the IBHO measurement. Corresponding handover counters in HO measurement are updated normally in addition to this counter.

counter_name_alias: IBHO ATT TO GSM ANE N01
counter_description: Number of IMSI-based handover attempts from the GSM to the GSM authorised network because of the coverage of the GSM cell of equivalent PLMN.  Failure of the attempts can be seen in the counter IBHO UNS TO GSM ANE N01 of the IBHO measurement. Corresponding handover counters in HO measurement are updated normally in addition to this counter.

counter_name_alias: IBHO ATT TO UTRAN ANE N05
counter_description: Number of IMSI-based handover attempts from the GSM to the UTRAN authorised network because of the coverage of the UTRAN cell of equivalent PLMN.   Failure of the attempts can be seen in the counter IBHO UNS TO UTRAN ANE N05 of the IBHO measurement. Corresponding handover counters in HO measurement are updated normally in addition to this counter.

counter_name_alias: IBHO ATT TO GSM ANE N08
counter_description: Number of IMSI-based handover attempts from the GSM to the GSM authorised network because of the coverage of the GSM cell of equivalent PLMN.   Failure of the attempts can be seen in the counter IBHO UNS TO GSM ANE N08 of the IBHO measurement. Corresponding handover counters in HO measurement are updated normally in addition to this counter.

counter_name_alias: DTM ALLOCATIONS INITIAL
counter_description: Number of initial DTM allocations made. Initial DTM allocation is a procedure where DTM resources are allocated to a DTM-capable MS that does not have a DTM allocation yet (the CS connection needs to be moved from the CS territory to the PS territory).

counter_name_alias: DTM RELEASES DUE CS RELEASE
counter_description: Number of DTM call release procedures where the CS connection is released normally during dual transfer mode.

counter_description: Number of rejected radio network handover attempts because of an ongoing handover to a TRX of another BCXU unit  Two counters of the Handover measurement are incremented along with this DX cause: - Number of forced BSC internal handover attempts due to TRX reallocation to another BCXU unit (004300). - Number of forced BSC external handover attempts due to TRX reallocation to another BCXU unit. (004301).

counter_name_alias: NO RESP TO RADIO RES REQ
counter_description: Number of failures in reserving a target channel during HO signalling.  Impact: HO attempt fails  Reason for the impact: BSC internal signalling.

counter_name_alias: MS IS LOST
counter_description: Number of lost MSs after a HANDOVER/ASSIGNMENT command during handovers.  Dependencies: - In BSC-internal HOs the new channel is cleared with DX cause 511. - In external HOs the old channel is cleared with the cause value set by the MSC.  Impact: - HO attempt fails. - Call is cleared.  Reason for the impact: MS, BSS

counter_name_alias: HO DENIED ASSIGN
counter_description: Number of times when the HO is not allowed to be started because an assignment procedure is in progress.  Impact: HO attempt interrupted

counter_name_alias: AIV TIMEOUT
counter_description: Number of timeouts in the AIVPRB that are related to the internal communication of the BSC.

counter_name_alias: CH TYPE MISMATCH
counter_description: The radio interface data rate requirement, included in the normal ASSIGNMENT_REQUEST or the HANDOVER_REQUEST message, is totally contradictory with the TCH channel rate request of the channel type IE.  The TCH channel rate request, or the data rate requirement, included in the ASSIGNMENT_REQUEST message related to the IN_CALL_MODIFICATION message or the FACCH call setup, is totally contradictory with the type of the TCH on which the call is maintained.  Impact:The assignment procedure fails on A interface, or in case of a handover, the handover attempt fails.

counter_name_alias: AIV CONN REFRESH TIMEOUT
counter_description: The A interface connection is refreshed from time to time during a call. This counter indicates that the timer for the connection refresh procedure has expired.  Dependencies: Counters 001078, 001079, 001080, 001087, 001088 and 001089 are updated with this counter.  Impact: Call cleared.

counter_name_alias: RC0 REJ DUE EME CALL
counter_description: Number of times when the hunting queue is full and an emergency call has taken priority over an ordinary call.  Counters 001078, 001079, 001080, 001087, 001088 and 001089 are updated with this counter.  Impact: Call attempt fails.

counter_name_alias: A TSL BLOCKED
counter_description: Number of assignments of a circuit that is blocked.

counter_name_alias: A CRCT REMOVED
counter_description: Number of speech circuits that have been removed from use.

counter_name_alias: M DIRECTED RETRY
counter_description: Number of messages received from the MSC that concern directed retry.

counter_name_alias: M EQUIPMENT FAIL
counter_description: Number of messages received from the MSC that concern equipment failures.

counter_name_alias: M NO RADIO RES AVAIL
counter_description: Number of messages received from the MSC which report that there are no radio resources available.

counter_name_alias: M NO SUPP REDUNDANCY LVL
counter_description: Number of Internal Handover Required Reject messages from MSC which report that requested redundancy level is not supported.

counter_name_alias: REGENERATION SECTION BACKGROUND BLOCK ERRORS
counter_description: An errored block is a block in which one or more bits have an error. B1 byte in the Section Overhead Header (SOH) is used for regenerator section / section error monitoring using the Bit Interleaved Parity 8 (BIP-8) code, in an even parity. The BIP-8 is computed over all the bits of the previous STM frame after scrambling, and is placed in byte B1 of the current frame before scrambling. In this case the block means STM-1/OC3 frame.

counter_name_alias: PATH TERMINATION SECTION 1 ERRORED SECONDS AT THE NEAR END
counter_description: Path termination section errored second at the near end. The number of seconds with one or more errored blocks or at least one defect. At the end of each one second interval the contents of the counters are obtained by the relevant managed objects. The objects are the path termination section (B3) errors, AU-AIS, LOP, PLM, TIM, UNEQ and LCD. In this case the block means virtual container.

counter_name_alias: PATH TERMINATION SECTION 1 SEVERELY ERRORED
counter_description: Path termination section severely errored seconds at the near end. The number of one second periods, which contain more or equal threshold errored blocks or at least one defect. The threshold can be handled by SDH/SONET Interface Configuration Handling YAN MML. At the end of each one second interval, the contents of the counters may be obtained by the relevant managed objects. The objects are the path termination section (B3) errors, AU-AIS, LOP, PLM, TIM, UNEQ, and LCD. In this case the block means virtual container/virtual tributary. During the SES condition, counter Path termination section 1 errored seconds at the near end 513016 is also incremented.

counter_name_alias: MULTIPLEX SECTION LINE BACKGROUND BLOCK ERRORS AT THE FAR END
counter_description: An errored block is a block in which one or more bits have an error. M1 byte conveys the count of errored blocks, which is calculated by the far end from its receiving blocks by using B2 bytes at multiplexer level. B2 bytes are the bytes allocated for a Multiplex section line error monitoring function, which is Bit Interleaved Parity 24 (BIP-24) code using even parity. The BIP-24 is computed over all bits of the previous STM frame exluding RSOH and is placed in byte B2 of the current frame. In this case the block means STM-1/OC3 frame.

counter_name_alias: PATH TERMINATION SECTION 3 UNAVAILABLE SECONDS AT THE FAR END
counter_description: A period of unavailable time begins at the start of ten consecutive SES events. These ten seconds are considered to be part of the unavailable time. A new period of available time begins at the start of ten consecutive non-SES events. These ten seconds are considered to be part of the available time.

counter_name_alias: PATH TERMINATION SECTION 3 BACKGROUND BLOCK ERRORS AT THE FAR END
counter_description: An errored block is a block in which one or more bits have an error. G1 byte in the section overhead header (SOH) is used for path termination section error monitoring using Bit Interleaved Parity 8 (BIP-8) code, in an even parity. The BIP-8 is computed over all the bits of the previous virtual container/virtual tributary (VC-12 over VC- 3 or VC-12 over VC-4 according to the configuration) and is placed in byte B3 of the current frame. In this case the block means virtual container/virtual tributary.

counter_name_alias: M3UA SCTP PACKETS SENT
counter_description: Number of data packets sent of the SCTP per an M3UA association, excluding SCTP control packets.

counter_name_alias: MAC-HS PDU RETRANSMISSION DISTRIBUTION - CLASS 0
counter_description: The number of MAC-hs PDUs or MAC-ehs PDUs correctly delivered without retransmissions.

counter_name_alias: MAC-HS PDU RETRANSMISSION DISTRIBUTION - CLASS 5
counter_description: The number of MAC-hs PDUs or MAC-ehs PDUs correctly delivered with more than 4 retransmissions.

counter_name_alias: REPORTED CQI DISTRIBUTION - CLASS 16
counter_description: Number of reported Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) values 16.

counter_name_alias: REPORTED CQI DISTRIBUTION - CLASS 23
counter_description: Number of reported Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) values 23.

counter_name_alias: REPORTED CQI DISTRIBUTION - CLASS 27
counter_description: Number of reported Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) values 27.

counter_name_alias: ORIGINAL MAC-HS PDU TRANSMISSION WITH 2 CODE BY 16QAM
counter_description: Number of original MAC-hs PDU transmissions with 2 code by 16QAM modulation.

counter_name_alias: ORIGINAL MAC-HS PDU TRANSMISSION WITH 3 CODE BY 16QAM
counter_description: Number of original MAC-hs PDU transmissions with 3 code by 16QAM modulation.

counter_name_alias: ORIGINAL MAC-HS PDU TRANSMISSION WITH 7 CODE BY QPSK
counter_description: Number of original MAC-hs PDU transmissions with 7 codes using QPSK modulation.

counter_name_alias: MAC-HS PDU RETRANSMISSION WITH 9 CODE BY QPSK
counter_description: Number of retransmitted MAC-hs PDUs with 9 codes using QPSK modulation.

counter_name_alias: MAC-HS PDU RETRANSMISSION WITH 9 CODE BY 16QAM
counter_description: Number of retransmitted MAC-hs PDUs with 9 codes using 16QAM modulation.

counter_name_alias: MAC-E PDU RETRANSMISSIONS 4 COUNTER
counter_description: Number of MAC-e PDUs that are received correctly with four retransmissions in E-DCH Serving Cell.This counter is also applicable for MAC-i.

counter_name_alias: HSUPA AVERAGE MAC-D THROUGHPUT
counter_description: Average HSUPA MAC-d throughput [kilobits/s] using the average over the measurement period samples.

counter_name_alias: HSUPA UL MINIMUM PHYSICAL CHANNEL POWER
counter_description: Minimum received HSUPA power using the average over the measurement period. Note: In case when E-DCH load factor is zero (no users in the cell), then HSUPA Power is set to minimum (Max=Min=Avg = -112 dbm). If counter is not pegged at all in measurement period, value 0 is returned.

counter_name_alias: HS-DSCH CREDIT REDUCTIONS DUE TO IUB DELAY
counter_description: Number of 10ms congestion control iterations in which the Iub throughput of connections originating from CRNC was controlled by Congestion Control based on trigger "the measured average delay build-up was over minimum delay threshold but below middle delay threshold". Conservatively, the value contains also the iterations directly following the initial total credit reduction until total credits granted to RNC recover and exceed the measured Iub throughput at the time of previous congestion detection by half or until a new throughput reduction is applied with different cause. All cells controlled by same congestion control entity display identical values in this counter because the Iub resource shared by congestion control is common for them. Note that only one of the M5000C176...C178 or M5000C453 may increment by 2 in 20ms iteration.

counter_name_alias: HS-DSCH CREDIT REDUCTIONS DUE TO FRAME LOSS
counter_description: Number of 10ms congestion control iterations in which the Iub throughput of connections originating from CRNC was controlled by Congestion Control based on trigger "frame losses detected based on sequence number discontinuity or CRC check". Conservatively, the value contains also the iterations directly following the initial total credit reduction until total credits granted to RNC recover and exceed the measured Iub throughput at the time of previous congestion detection by half or until a new throughput reduction is applied with different cause. All cells controlled by same congestion control entity display identical values in this counter because the Iub resource shared by congestion control is common for them. Note that only one of the M5000C176...C178 or M5000C453 may increment by 2 in 20ms iteration.

counter_name_alias: UE SERVING POWER HEADROOM VALUE 08
counter_description: UE Power Headroom value reported by the UE in the serving radio link set is 8.

counter_name_alias: UE SERVING POWER HEADROOM VALUE 16
counter_description: UE Power Headroom value reported by the UE in the serving radio link set is 16.

counter_name_alias: UE NON-SERVING POWER HEADROOM VALUE 04
counter_description: UE Power Headroom value reported by the UE in the non-serving radio link set is 4.

counter_name_alias: UE NON-SERVING POWER HEADROOM VALUE 07
counter_description: UE Power Headroom value reported by the UE in the non-serving radio link set is 7.

counter_name_alias: UE NON-SERVING POWER HEADROOM VALUE 28
counter_description: UE Power Headroom value reported by the UE in the non-serving radio link set is 28.

counter_name_alias: NON-SERVING E-RGCH COMMANDS
counter_description: Number of non-serving E-RGCH commands sent due to power overload.

counter_name_alias: FRACTIONAL LOAD VALUE DISTRIBUTION - CLASS 01
counter_description: Rise Over Thermal in Fractional load:L = 1 - (Pnoise/Ptotal), Ptotal>=Pnoise. The fractional load is calculated in the normal scheduling operation matches to limits defined for class 1 (0 < L <= 0.05).

counter_name_alias: FRACTIONAL LOAD VALUE DISTRIBUTION - CLASS 14
